4 A BILL
5 TO BE ENTITLED
6 AN ACT
7
8
9 Relating to Marshall County; to amend Section
10 45-48-241.05, Code of Alabama 1975, to further provide for the
11 compensation of the county revenue commissioner.
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
13 Section 1. Section 45-48-241.05, Code of Alabama 1975,
14 is amended to read as follows:
15 "§45-48-241.05
16 (a) The county revenue commissioner shall collect and
17 pay into the general fund of the county all fees, percentages,
18 commissions, and other allowances which the tax assessor or
19 tax collector of the county is authorized and directed to
20 charge or collect for the performance of any duty imposed on
21 the county revenue commissioner.
22 (b) As compensation for the performance of the duties
23 of his or her office, the county revenue commissioner shall
24 receive an annual salary of sixty-seven thousand five hundred
25 dollars ($67,500).
26 (c) Effective beginning with the next term of office,
27 the annual salary of the county revenue commissioner shall be
28 one hundred six thousand, seven hundred eighty-one dollars
Page 1

one hundred six thousand, seven hundred eighty-one dollars
